  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of sanitation and hygiene services and facilities to South Sudanese Refugees in El Salaam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to provide sanitation and hygiene services and facilities to South Sudanese refugees in White Nile State in two localities (El Salam and Al Jabalian localities). This project will mainly focus on improving sanitation and hygiene gaps/needs of South Sudanese refugees in the ten camps Alagaya, Dabat Bosin, and new camp relocated from Alganaa, Al Jamiya, Khor Al Warel, Um Sangor, Al Redis I, Al Redis II, Jouri, and Al Kashafa, located in El Salam and El Jabalian localities thereby reducing instances of water-borne or water-related diseases, for 276,217  refugees. Delivery of the project will be through rehabilitation of existing latrines, desludging of the existing communal latrines, construction of improved trench emergency communal latrines, construction of shared household/family latrines, decommissioning of out of use communal latrines, operation and maintenance of shared family latrines, communal and household latrines; provision of personal, household and community sanitation and hygiene services; and capacity strengthening of sanitation and hygiene structures in the camps. The project is part and parcel of the Sudan Country Refugee Response Plan (CRP), UNHCR Sudan and WASH sector 2022 priorities . The processes of project implementation will incorporate efforts and inputs of Ministry of Health (MoH), Commissioner for Refugees (COR), the Water Environmental Sanitation Project (WES), UNHCR, UNICEF, WASH partners, and Humanitarian Aid Commission (HAC). Project design is informed by WASH sector strategies and recommendations.</narrative>
  </description>
